HEADWORD: faze
<hw>faze</hw> <pr>(f⟦amac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to
become disconcerted or disturbed. A variant form of
<er>Feeze</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The perpetual need to learn new software
doesn't <ex>faze</ex> him.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source> ]</p>

